<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-17T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-17T16:00:00-05:00" n="616" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d616">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">693.003/438: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-17T16:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">November
                                            17, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>Your October 2, 2 p.m.</p>
                            <p>Arnold<note n="64" xml:id="d616fn64">Julean Arnold, Commercial
                                    Attaché in China.</note> is designated to represent the United
                                States Government on the international tariff commission to meet at
                                Shanghai December 1 for the revision of the tariff. He should bear
                                in mind <pb facs="0744" n="642" xml:id="pg_642"/> the understanding
                                of this Government stated in the Department’s October 15, 6 p.m.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>